    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n6555" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">νῦν</span></b> : <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">now</span>, freq.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">νῦν δή, νῦν αὖ</span>, and esp. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">νῦν δέ</span>, ‘as it is,’ ‘as it was,’ contrasting
          the real state of the case with a supposed one, <i><span class="en">Il. 1.417</span></i>. In the uses that are not
          strictly temporal <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">νῦν</span> differs from
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">νύν</span> only in form (quantity), not in
          meaning, <i><span class="en">Il. 10.175</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
